76

BALLADS

So desperately they boarded us For all our valiant shot,

Threescore of their best fighting men Upon our dccks were got;

And lo! at their first entranccs Full thirty did we kill,

And thus we cleared with specd the deck Of our Angel Gabriel.

With that their three ships boarded us Again with might and main,

But still our noble Englishmen Cried out, ‘A fig for Spain! ²

Though seven times they boarded us At last we showed our skill,

And made them feel what men we were On the Angel Gabriel.

Seven hours this fight continued: So many men lay dead,

With Spanish blood for fathoms round The sea was coloured red.

Five hundred of their fighting men We there outright did kill,

And many more were hurt and maimed By our Angel Gabriel.

Then, seeing of these bloody spoils, 'l'he rest made haste away:

For why, they said, it was no boot The longer there to stay.
